  "prompt": "Is there any device by which I can on/off my electrical device at desired frequency?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several devices and methods to control electrical devices at a desired frequency:\n\n1. Timer Switches\n- Mechanical or digital timers\n- Can schedule on/off cycles\n- Suitable for appliances, lights, etc.\n\n2. Smart Plugs/Outlets\n- Wi-Fi or Bluetooth enabled\n- Controlled via smartphone apps\n- Programmable schedules\n- Some support custom frequency settings\n\n3. Programmable Relays\n- Industrial-grade switching devices\n- Precise frequency and timing control\n- Used in automation and industrial applications\n\n4. Digital Timer Controllers\n- Highly customizable\n- Set complex on/off patterns\n- Used in research, experiments, and specialized applications\n\n5. Frequency Generators\n- Electronic devices that produce precise signals\n- Can control switching at specific frequencies\n- Used in scientific and technical settings\n\n6. Home Automation Systems\n- Smart home platforms like Home Assistant\n- Advanced scheduling and frequency control\n- Integration with multiple devices\n\n7. Cycle Timers\n- Specific for repetitive on/off sequences\n- Used in agricultural, industrial settings\n\nThe best choice depends on your specific requirements, budget, and application.\n\nWould you like more details about any of these options?",
